1
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:17,867
Red, I also want to clarify
some things.

2
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,300
I don't want to quickly
judge your mom.

3
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:22,267
Don't believe your mom.

4
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,500
She'll do everything to ruin
my mom's reputation.

5
00:00:24,633 --> 00:00:26,433
I feel bad for what my mom
had been through

6
00:00:26,567 --> 00:00:28,833
at the hands of Uncle Zandro
and Mama Rina.

7
00:00:28,967 --> 00:00:32,333
If there's someone who wants
to harm us, it's your mother.

8
00:00:32,467 --> 00:00:34,567
I've already told her everything
that had happened to me.

9
00:00:34,733 --> 00:00:37,433
But she still chose Red
and his family.

10
00:00:37,567 --> 00:00:40,633
She might get more upset
with you for what you did.

11
00:00:40,767 --> 00:00:42,400
I need to be tough.

12
00:00:42,533 --> 00:00:45,433
If not, she might really end up
choosing Rina's family.

13
00:00:45,567 --> 00:00:47,500
Don't you feel bad for her,
Amanda?

14
00:00:47,633 --> 00:00:50,300
I have to do this for her sake.

15
00:00:50,433 --> 00:00:51,900
I heard you haven't eaten
anything yet.

16
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:53,433
I don't think that's right.

17
00:00:53,567 --> 00:00:55,000
What is right then?

18
00:00:55,133 --> 00:00:57,033
Controlling my life?

19
00:00:57,167 --> 00:00:59,800
You can't persuade me
with your hunger strike.

20
00:00:59,933 --> 00:01:01,000
Eat something.

21
00:01:01,133 --> 00:01:03,667
I can sense that Red will come
to get her.

22
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:05,133
Do you already have a plan?

23
00:01:05,267 --> 00:01:06,600
I want to take her away
from here...

24
00:01:06,733 --> 00:01:09,500
to a place where Red
can't find her.

25
00:01:09,667 --> 00:01:12,833
If I were you, I'd be obedient
to my mom.

26
00:01:12,967 --> 00:01:16,167
If not, she's going to take you
away from here.

27
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:18,300
Where will my mom take me?

28
00:01:18,433 --> 00:01:20,300
I can't leave.

29
00:01:20,433 --> 00:01:22,167
Please, help me escape
from here.

30
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:23,333
I'm going to lose my mind.

31
00:01:23,467 --> 00:01:24,767
I can't bear it.

32
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:26,267
I'm outside your house already.

33
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:27,833
Okay. I'll go downstairs now.

34
00:01:27,967 --> 00:01:31,400
Okay, let's go. Your mom might
arrive any moment now.

35
00:01:31,533 --> 00:01:32,700
I'm glad you're out of jail.

36
00:01:32,833 --> 00:01:34,233
I was able to post bail.

37
00:01:34,367 --> 00:01:37,833
But Amanda won't leave me alone.

38
00:01:37,967 --> 00:01:40,900
Because she has Lucho,
who is powerful.

39
00:01:41,067 --> 00:01:42,367
What do you want me to do?

40
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:47,433
I know what we can do.

41
00:01:47,567 --> 00:01:49,200
Oh my god, Auntie.

42
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:51,833
Auntie, thank you so much.

43
00:01:51,967 --> 00:01:54,900
I know you lied to my mom
so many times for me.

44
00:01:55,033 --> 00:01:57,300
- I'm sorry, Auntie.
- I love you so much.

45
00:01:57,433 --> 00:02:00,367
- I will never forget you.
- I love you so much.

46
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:02,867
Red! Red, are you okay?

47
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:03,867
Does anything hurt?
I'm okay.

48
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:05,933
Yen, we have to go.

49
00:02:06,067 --> 00:02:07,867
I parked the car just
across the house.

50
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,700
Red! That's my mom!

51
00:02:09,833 --> 00:02:11,133
Come on!

52
00:02:11,267 --> 00:02:13,967
I'm already here, Rina.

53
00:02:31,633 --> 00:02:34,700
My stomach hurts so much.

54
00:02:34,833 --> 00:02:36,100
Your stomach hurts?

55
00:02:36,233 --> 00:02:37,100
Okay.

56
00:02:37,233 --> 00:02:38,700
I'll be there.

57
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:41,167
- I'll check on Dindi.
- Okay.

58
00:03:16,533 --> 00:03:18,467
Hello, Zandro?

59
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:21,000
I did what you told me.

60
00:03:21,167 --> 00:03:23,033
I broke Lucho's car brakes.

61
00:03:23,167 --> 00:03:24,867
Very good!

62
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:27,300
But I hope you did it well.

63
00:03:27,433 --> 00:03:28,867
This is the end of him, Rina.

64
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,333
I messed up with his car brakes.

65
00:03:31,467 --> 00:03:34,867
He won't notice it at first,
but as he drives faster,

66
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:39,200
the brake fluid will also
leak rapidly.

67
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:43,800
His brakes will surely fail
if he drives faster.

68
00:03:43,933 --> 00:03:46,967
You better leave that place.

69
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:50,333
Someone might see you.

70
00:03:50,467 --> 00:03:52,200
Let's call each other sometime
later.

71
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:53,833
Lie low for now.

72
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,100
Yes, Rina.

73
00:04:10,167 --> 00:04:12,733
You'll die soon...

74
00:04:12,867 --> 00:04:14,633
Amanda.

75
00:04:21,367 --> 00:04:23,467
Dindi.

76
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:26,467
You're making me nervous.

77
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,167
Are you okay?

78
00:04:28,333 --> 00:04:31,700
Aren't you hungry?

79
00:04:31,833 --> 00:04:34,800
Are you trying to lose weight?

80
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:36,533
- Promise, I'm okay now.
- Are you sure?

81
00:04:36,667 --> 00:04:37,633
Earlier, I felt dizzy.

82
00:04:37,767 --> 00:04:41,567
Maybe my eye grade went up.

83
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:42,933
That's why.

84
00:04:43,067 --> 00:04:47,867
Okay. But don't self-medicate,
please?

85
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,133
We can go to the doctor.

86
00:04:50,267 --> 00:04:53,533
I can bring you to the hospital.

87
00:04:53,667 --> 00:04:55,367
We have money now, Dindi.

88
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:57,867
We don't have to save up.

89
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,133
It's okay.

90
00:04:59,267 --> 00:05:01,900
I will bring you
to the hospital.

91
00:05:02,067 --> 00:05:02,933
Don't be shy.

92
00:05:03,067 --> 00:05:04,933
- No, Amanda.
- I won't be stingy.

93
00:05:05,067 --> 00:05:08,233
No, Amanda. I really am okay.

94
00:05:08,367 --> 00:05:09,433
I'll stay here for now.

95
00:05:09,567 --> 00:05:11,867
Maybe just a nap,
and I'll be okay.

96
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,033
Promise. Okay. Don't worry.

97
00:05:13,167 --> 00:05:14,467
Okay.

98
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:16,433
I'll go and check on Eden,
too, okay?

99
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:18,367
Call me when you need anything.

100
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:20,200
- Do you want to eat?
- I'm okay.

101
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:21,200
I'll send you some food.

102
00:05:21,333 --> 00:05:22,633
I'll just take a nap.

103
00:05:22,767 --> 00:05:24,233
- Thank you, Amanda.
- Okay.

104
00:05:24,367 --> 00:05:26,500
- All right.
- Thanks, Sis.

105
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,967
It's auntie.

106
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:57,733
Hello?

107
00:05:57,867 --> 00:06:00,100
Hurry up and leave! Hurry up!

108
00:06:00,233 --> 00:06:02,167
Hurry!

109
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,800
Let's hurry up.

110
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:12,600
Eden?

111
00:06:19,567 --> 00:06:21,000
Eden.

112
00:06:28,133 --> 00:06:29,533
Eden?

113
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:37,767
Eden!

114
00:06:39,967 --> 00:06:41,333
Eden!

115
00:06:49,167 --> 00:06:52,967
Eden!

116
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:57,467
Bruno's there!

117
00:07:02,467 --> 00:07:03,967
I knew it!

118
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:04,967
Mom!

119
00:07:05,100 --> 00:07:06,500
- Where are you going?
- Mom, let me go!

120
00:07:06,633 --> 00:07:08,633
No! You're not coming with him!

121
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:14,300
Come in!

122
00:07:19,633 --> 00:07:20,700
What is it?

123
00:07:22,367 --> 00:07:23,433
Ma'am Rina,

124
00:07:23,567 --> 00:07:27,767
I was going to tell Sir Victor
that Red had gone out.

125
00:07:27,900 --> 00:07:29,067
What?

126
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,833
He left with his car.

127
00:07:32,967 --> 00:07:34,700
Don't tell Victor about it.

128
00:07:34,833 --> 00:07:36,000
I'll take care of it.

129
00:07:36,133 --> 00:07:37,000
Okay.

130
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,600
There's only one place
he would go.

131
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:50,333
We already have proved
to everyone

132
00:07:50,467 --> 00:07:51,633
that we love each other.

133
00:07:51,767 --> 00:07:53,033
I will fight for Yenyen
until the end.

134
00:07:53,167 --> 00:07:54,600
I can't live without her.

135
00:07:54,733 --> 00:07:56,067
I don't need your opinion.

136
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,533
You ruined everything!

137
00:07:57,667 --> 00:07:58,533
Mom, please.
- Let me go.
- No!

138
00:07:59,633 --> 00:08:00,367
- No!
- Let me go!

139
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:01,900
You're not leaving.

140
00:08:02,033 --> 00:08:05,667
Why can't you understand that
Red isn't meant for you?

141
00:08:18,267 --> 00:08:19,267
Dindi.

142
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,733
Where's your sister?

143
00:08:22,867 --> 00:08:24,567
Amanda?

144
00:08:24,700 --> 00:08:25,767
Yes.

145
00:08:32,433 --> 00:08:33,367
Rina?

146
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:35,067
Hello, Zandro.

147
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,133
Where are you?

148
00:08:36,267 --> 00:08:37,300
Why?

149
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:40,000
Are you still outside
the Madrigals' house?

150
00:08:40,133 --> 00:08:42,300
No, I'm back in my cave.

151
00:08:42,433 --> 00:08:43,867
What's the matter?

152
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,467
Red isn't here.

153
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:50,167
There's only one place
he would go.

154
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:52,600
He'll look for Eden.

155
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,900
What do you want me to do?

156
00:08:56,067 --> 00:08:57,333
Go back there.

157
00:08:59,333 --> 00:09:01,500
Spy on them.

158
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:02,433
Just...

159
00:09:02,567 --> 00:09:03,933
just check on Red, okay?

160
00:09:04,067 --> 00:09:08,233
Make sure he won't get hurt
by Amanda.

161
00:09:08,733 --> 00:09:10,700
I'll just change my clothes
and go there too.

162
00:09:10,833 --> 00:09:12,367
Wait for me, okay?

163
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:13,800
Copy, Rina.

164
00:09:15,067 --> 00:09:16,133
All right.

165
00:09:30,033 --> 00:09:31,600
She walked me to my room.

166
00:09:31,733 --> 00:09:33,033
You two were together
earlier, right?

167
00:09:33,167 --> 00:09:35,633
Yes, but she left right after.

168
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:37,667
Where did she go?

169
00:09:39,167 --> 00:09:40,100
I already know, Mom.

170
00:09:40,233 --> 00:09:41,400
Please! I know everything now!

171
00:09:41,533 --> 00:09:44,267
That you can't accept Red!

172
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:47,167
I know that whenever
and no matter what I do,

173
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:50,600
you will never accept
our relationship.

174
00:09:50,733 --> 00:09:52,833
And I love you so much.

175
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:58,333
But let me choose
my own happiness, Mom.

176
00:09:58,467 --> 00:09:59,267
No.

177
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:02,200
Why can't you still
understand that?

178
00:10:02,367 --> 00:10:03,800
Because it hurts so much!

179
00:10:03,933 --> 00:10:05,033
I cannot accept it!

180
00:10:05,167 --> 00:10:06,167
I'm your mother,

181
00:10:06,300 --> 00:10:09,500
but I'm always at a disadvantage
with your decisions!

182
00:10:09,633 --> 00:10:11,400
Do you really love me?

183
00:10:13,133 --> 00:10:17,400
Red and I are leaving, but that
doesn't mean I don't love you.

184
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:18,633
No...

185
00:10:18,767 --> 00:10:22,067
I love you so much, and it will
never change.

186
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:26,533
We're leaving to keep you
from getting hurt.

187
00:10:26,667 --> 00:10:28,767
We'll just leave.

188
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:32,767
We will start fulfilling our
dream of having our own family.

189
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:33,933
No!

190
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:36,367
You're not getting married.

191
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:38,267
We will get married whether you
like it or not!

192
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:42,000
All of us will die before the
two of you can get married.

193
00:10:42,133 --> 00:10:43,467
- Mom, let me go!
- Yen, let's go, let's go.

194
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:44,800
- Mom, let me go!
- No!

195
00:10:44,933 --> 00:10:46,867
- Help!
- Miss Amanda!

196
00:10:48,267 --> 00:10:49,533
Lucho!

197
00:10:49,667 --> 00:10:51,000
Lucho!

198
00:10:51,133 --> 00:10:52,533
Amanda!

199
00:10:52,667 --> 00:10:53,533
Amanda!

200
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:55,900
Lucho!

201
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,000
- This is not my key!
- Hurry up! We have no time!

202
00:11:24,133 --> 00:11:25,067
Eden!

203
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:27,167
Lucho!

204
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:28,767
Catch them!

205
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:30,200
Lucho!

206
00:11:31,067 --> 00:11:32,900
Red, they use this car.

207
00:11:33,033 --> 00:11:33,967
Let's go, Yen.

208
00:11:42,533 --> 00:11:43,900
Lucho!

209
00:11:44,033 --> 00:11:46,767
- Lucho, it's Eden!
- Amanda, what happened?

210
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:48,067
Lucho, that's them!

211
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,033
Hey!

212
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:54,200
- What are we going to do?
- Come on, let's chase them!

213
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:22,367
Red, where are we going?

214
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:23,567
Can't my mom follow us?

215
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:25,700
I'm sure she'll try
to follow us.

216
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,100
I need to take you away for now.

217
00:12:31,233 --> 00:12:33,800
I'll make sure that we will
never part again.

218
00:12:35,333 --> 00:12:40,333
I don't know where we will go.

219
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:43,367
But what matters is that they
can't follow us.

220
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:46,500
No one will mess
with us anymore.

221
00:12:46,633 --> 00:12:49,967
Sometimes I miss the island.

222
00:12:50,133 --> 00:12:52,800
Because it's so peaceful there.

223
00:12:52,933 --> 00:12:56,100
We forget about our problems.

224
00:12:57,933 --> 00:12:59,800
It feels like we're not
in the real world.

225
00:12:59,933 --> 00:13:02,833
I want to forget all our
problems, Red.

226
00:13:02,967 --> 00:13:07,267
This island is so special to me.

227
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:09,767
I will never forget this place.

228
00:13:09,900 --> 00:13:12,933
We met on an island.

229
00:13:13,067 --> 00:13:16,233
And we fell in love
on an island.

230
00:13:17,900 --> 00:13:23,867
And we found our way back
to each other on an island.

231
00:13:25,167 --> 00:13:28,233
The next time we return
to an island,

232
00:13:28,367 --> 00:13:31,033
we'll say each other's vows
for real.

233
00:13:31,167 --> 00:13:34,067
Because that's where
we are going to get married.

234
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:35,267
I like that.

235
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:36,700
Do you like that?

236
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:40,900
Shall we?

237
00:13:41,933 --> 00:13:43,033
It's like when we were
on the island.

238
00:13:43,167 --> 00:13:45,533
It's just the two of us.

239
00:13:45,667 --> 00:13:47,867
No one is there aside from us.

240
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:53,633
No one is controlling our lives
but ourselves.

241
00:13:58,367 --> 00:14:00,333
There they are! Follow them!

242
00:14:00,467 --> 00:14:02,167
Red.

243
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:04,633
Red, someone is following us.

244
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:15,900
Red, they're following us!

245
00:14:16,033 --> 00:14:16,900
Drive faster!

246
00:14:17,033 --> 00:14:18,300
Faster!

247
00:14:18,433 --> 00:14:20,100
Red, what do we do?

248
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,033
Overtake that car!

249
00:14:40,167 --> 00:14:42,133
Boss, we can't do that.

250
00:14:42,267 --> 00:14:43,233
There are a lot of cars
in the other lane.

251
00:14:43,367 --> 00:14:44,967
Okay. Just try to come closer.

252
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:47,133
Don't let them slip out
of your sight.

253
00:14:49,233 --> 00:14:51,700
This is our chance
to escape them.

254
00:14:53,733 --> 00:14:55,733
Faster, Bruno!

255
00:14:55,867 --> 00:14:57,833
They might escape from us!

256
00:15:02,433 --> 00:15:03,900
They overtook a truck!

257
00:15:05,767 --> 00:15:08,200
Overtake that truck!

258
00:15:21,533 --> 00:15:23,867
They haven't overtaken
the truck yet.

259
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,933
Go, overtake!

260
00:15:27,567 --> 00:15:28,867
There, to the right.

261
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:35,800
Where are they?

262
00:15:35,967 --> 00:15:38,167
Where are they?

263
00:15:40,067 --> 00:15:42,333
- Where are they?
- Where did they go?

264
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:46,300
Are they still behind us?

265
00:15:48,133 --> 00:15:52,400
Maybe they took a turn,
and we missed it!

266
00:15:52,533 --> 00:15:54,533
I think we lost them already.

267
00:15:54,667 --> 00:15:58,833
No one's following us anymore.

268
00:15:58,967 --> 00:16:00,033
Wait!

269
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:02,000
- Didn't you see them?
- Maybe they escaped already.

270
00:16:02,133 --> 00:16:03,167
They can't escape!

271
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,600
Come on, Bruno!

272
00:16:04,733 --> 00:16:05,600
Drive faster!

273
00:16:05,733 --> 00:16:07,967
Hold on! Let's go back!

274
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:09,767
- Pull over.
- Make a U-turn.

275
00:16:09,933 --> 00:16:12,467
Let's go back!

276
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:14,300
They can't just disappear!

277
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:16,500
Go on, go back!

278
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:42,367
Rina.

279
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:43,567
So?

280
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:45,600
Did you see Red?

281
00:16:45,733 --> 00:16:47,033
- Red?
- Yes.

282
00:16:47,167 --> 00:16:51,200
Red isn't here,
but his car is here.

283
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:07,433
Finally, Yen, I can take you
away from here now.

284
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:10,567
No one can separate us anymore.

285
00:17:12,700 --> 00:17:17,267
When your mother took you,
I thought I'd already lost you.

286
00:17:20,067 --> 00:17:23,400
I thought I would never
see you again.

287
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:27,833
That can't happen, Red.

288
00:17:27,967 --> 00:17:31,500
I can't live without you.

289
00:17:31,633 --> 00:17:39,467
I will fight for your love
as long as I can.

290
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:42,867
As you said, never give up.

291
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,833
Right?

292
00:17:44,967 --> 00:17:45,900
I will fight, Red.

293
00:17:46,033 --> 00:17:48,633
I won't give up on you.

294
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:53,400
I promise you that fighting
for me will be all worth it.

295
00:17:55,033 --> 00:17:58,100
Yen, I will make you happy

296
00:17:58,233 --> 00:18:00,500
I will make you and our future
child happy.

297
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:05,667
I will take you to a faraway
land.

298
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:11,133
It will be just us.

299
00:18:11,267 --> 00:18:14,333
No one can trouble us anymore.

300
00:18:14,467 --> 00:18:16,033
That's where we will start
our family.

301
00:18:16,167 --> 00:18:20,633
We'll have lots
of children there.

302
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:24,867
How many children do you want?

303
00:18:25,033 --> 00:18:27,300
A lot.

304
00:18:27,433 --> 00:18:33,467
Many little Red or little Yen
will greet me

305
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:35,867
when I go home from work.

306
00:18:37,167 --> 00:18:39,100
That's my dream.

307
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:41,367
That's the only thing that will
make me happy.

308
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:43,600
Their smiles when they greet me.

309
00:18:43,733 --> 00:18:45,333
I'll be content with that.

310
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:50,367
It will come true, Red.

311
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:53,700
I believe it will happen...

312
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:56,100
as long as we don't give up.

313
00:18:56,267 --> 00:18:58,000
We won't give up on each other.

314
00:19:00,167 --> 00:19:04,867
Yen, we will fill our house
with love.

315
00:19:25,367 --> 00:19:26,600
Where's my son?

316
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,767
I've been here for a while now.

317
00:19:29,933 --> 00:19:32,300
I didn't see Red
when I came back here.

318
00:19:32,433 --> 00:19:34,300
But I saw Amanda earlier.

319
00:19:34,433 --> 00:19:36,133
She left.

320
00:19:36,267 --> 00:19:37,833
Did she leave with the car?

321
00:19:37,967 --> 00:19:42,167
Yes. Using the car
with the broken brakes.

322
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:43,200
Wait.

323
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:50,467
If Red's car is here,
and Lucho's car isn't...

324
00:19:52,167 --> 00:19:54,633
They might have done something
to my son.

325
00:19:54,767 --> 00:19:59,767
Maybe they took Red
using the car!

326
00:20:06,833 --> 00:20:08,200
Red, why?

327
00:20:08,333 --> 00:20:09,533
What's wrong?

328
00:20:09,667 --> 00:20:11,333
Yen, the brake isn't working.

329
00:20:11,467 --> 00:20:13,800
What?

330
00:20:13,933 --> 00:20:15,700
Red, what do we do?

331
00:20:17,267 --> 00:20:19,600
Yen!

332
00:20:19,733 --> 00:20:21,400
Red, what?

333
00:20:21,533 --> 00:20:24,533
Yen, the only way for the car
to stop is to...

334
00:20:24,667 --> 00:20:25,533
I need to...

335
00:20:25,667 --> 00:20:27,067
I need to crash this somewhere,
Yen.

336
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:29,600
Red, no.

337
00:20:29,733 --> 00:20:32,400
Yen, this is the only way!

338
00:20:32,533 --> 00:20:34,100
Red, what about you?

339
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:35,500
What are you talking about? No!

340
00:20:35,667 --> 00:20:36,767
I won't let that happen!

341
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:39,367
Don't think about me. You need
to save yourself, okay?

342
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:41,233
When I say jump,
you should jump!

343
00:20:41,367 --> 00:20:42,267
Red, I don't want to!

344
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:43,300
We have no choice, Yen!

345
00:20:43,433 --> 00:20:46,100
- No, Red!
- You need to do as I say!

346
00:20:46,233 --> 00:20:47,300
Red, no!

347
00:20:47,433 --> 00:20:50,200
You need to do as I say!
We don't have a choice, Yen!

348
00:20:50,333 --> 00:20:51,967
I won't let you do it, Red.

349
00:20:59,300 --> 00:21:02,267
Red, what are you doing?

350
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:04,533
Red, what are you doing?

351
00:21:05,867 --> 00:21:07,467
On the count of three, Yen...

352
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:09,833
- One, two!
- Red, I don't want to!

353
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:12,000
Three!

354
00:21:13,467 --> 00:21:14,833
Go!

355
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:41,767
This is all your fault!

356
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:43,000
You are to blame!

357
00:21:43,167 --> 00:21:44,200
Why are you blaming me?

358
00:21:44,333 --> 00:21:45,600
Isn't this your plan?

359
00:21:45,733 --> 00:21:48,467
Didn't you tell me to cut
the brakes of Lucho's car?

360
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:50,167
Wait a minute.
Are you blaming me?

361
00:21:50,300 --> 00:21:54,300
And don't you raise your voice
at me, Zandro!

362
00:21:54,433 --> 00:21:55,467
Find my son!

363
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:56,833
That's what you should do!

364
00:21:56,967 --> 00:21:58,967
Don't tell me you're hiding
something from me?

365
00:21:59,100 --> 00:22:00,867
Victor, it's about Red...

366
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,433
Lucho!

367
00:22:02,567 --> 00:22:03,900
They can't disappear.

368
00:22:04,033 --> 00:22:06,700
Red can't take my daughter away!

369
00:22:06,833 --> 00:22:08,767
I can't lose her!

370
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:10,100
Yes?

371
00:22:10,233 --> 00:22:11,200
It's me.

372
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:13,700
I'm his father.

373
00:22:13,833 --> 00:22:15,367
What?

374
00:22:15,533 --> 00:22:17,200
Which hospital?
